Nollywood actress Tayo Sobola aka Sotayogaga has been preaching peace and oneness after the coronation for her new role as Queen Mother in Uke Kingdom, Nasarawa state. In her speech at the coronation, the excited actress thanked the people of Uke for deeming it fit to give such a huge responsibility and honor to her. She said, “I am super proud that as a Yoruba girl, I am here holding a staff of office in the Uke Kingdom and this is an indication that we should all preach one Nigeria and togetherness.”   Don’t marry if you aren’t a millionaire, Joro Olumofin…     Burna Boy gifts $3000 to singer who grabbed his foot     Singer Portable threatens to seduce married women   Read Also: Just the other day: A note to you Continuing, Sotayogaga said, “As the Queen mother, the palace would now begin to see the impact of women in decision making amongst others.” - Advertisement - Sobola was crowned the new Sarauniya (Queen Mother) of Uke Kingdom Nasarawa state by the Emir of Uke Kingdom, Alhaji Abdullah Hassan for her passion for woman empowerment and enlightenment.